@startuml
title Redundant Storage Architecture - Replication and Failover Sequence

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/interaction/sequence-diagram-style.iuml

actor "Cloud\nConsumers" as CC
participant "Storage Service\nGateway" as SSG
database "Primary Cloud\nStorage Device" as Primary
database "Secondary Cloud\nStorage Device" as Secondary
participant "LUNs\n(secondary)" as LUNS

== Normal operation ==
CC -> SSG : requests
SSG -> Primary : forward
Primary -> Secondary : (1) routine\nstorage replication

== Primary fails ==
note over Primary
  Failure: network connectivity,
  controller / hardware failure,
  or security breach
end note

CC -> SSG : requests
SSG -> Secondary : (2) redirect to\nsecondary
Secondary -> LUNS : (3) forward to LUNs
LUNS --> CC : data accessible

note right of Secondary
  Storage replication is a variation of
  resource replication; it can replicate
  partial or entire LUNs.
end note

@enduml
